WEBVTT

00:01.400 --> 00:04.280
As a lawyer for
the richest family in New York

00:04.400 --> 00:07.137
until his plane went down
in long island sound.

00:07.257 --> 00:09.932
He left me his biggest client,
the Darlings--

00:10.052 --> 00:11.433
Tripp, the empire builder...

00:11.553 --> 00:13.851
You lied to me. You said you knew
about the affair.

00:14.009 --> 00:15.080
I didn't know.

00:15.200 --> 00:17.188
Letitia,
the sophisticated socialite...

00:17.309 --> 00:19.400
Your father was my great love.

00:19.520 --> 00:20.658
Brian, the man of God...

00:20.778 --> 00:22.290
I lied to my wife
and daughters.

00:22.410 --> 00:23.880
I told them
that you were an orphan.

00:24.000 --> 00:25.980
Patrick,
the principled politician,

00:26.100 --> 00:27.680
Karen,
the professional divorcÃ©e...

00:27.800 --> 00:29.760
Karen, do not call me
on the home phone number.

00:29.888 --> 00:31.245
I'll always love you, too.

00:31.365 --> 00:33.380
And Jeremy and Juliet,
the well-behaved twins.

00:33.500 --> 00:35.367
She was my best friend
in the whole world.

00:35.487 --> 00:37.126
- I want you.
- If Juliet found out...

00:37.246 --> 00:38.627
She won't find out.

00:38.747 --> 00:39.980
You think Simon elder,

00:40.100 --> 00:42.680
the billionaire philanthropist,
blew up your father's plane?

00:42.800 --> 00:44.585
Simon elder is not the man
you think he is,

00:44.712 --> 00:46.225
and your boss isn't either.

00:56.426 --> 00:57.694
Morning, daddy.

00:58.200 --> 00:59.480
- Hey.
- Hi.

01:00.094 --> 01:01.603
I have to get you some new suits.

01:01.736 --> 01:04.144
The dry cleaner is starting to think
I have a thing for him.

01:04.286 --> 01:06.697
I'm sorry, I stayed here
at the office again.

01:06.817 --> 01:09.080
I been going through this pile
of donation requests.

01:09.200 --> 01:11.075
It's okay. We know you're busy.
It's all good.

01:11.195 --> 01:13.115
I just don't know how
I'm supposed to help people

01:13.198 --> 01:14.876
if I can't make time
to write the checks.

01:14.996 --> 01:16.760
The whole family
sleeps here now. Charming

01:16.889 --> 01:18.045
I work in a sweatshop.

01:18.579 --> 01:19.960
Pookie-kai, Daisy.

01:20.080 --> 01:21.879
Pookie-kai,
long time, no see.

01:21.999 --> 01:24.089
Pookie-kai?
What is pookie-kai?

01:24.209 --> 01:25.780
Secret girl stuff.

01:26.255 --> 01:27.880
Maybe we should go to my desk.

01:28.285 --> 01:29.361
Thanks, guys.

01:30.892 --> 01:32.389
- How are you?
- Nestly?

01:32.509 --> 01:34.615
I'm up to my ears hanging this
new show at the gallery,

01:34.695 --> 01:35.696
I'm reading three books,

01:35.777 --> 01:37.396
none of which I'm making
any headway in,

01:37.516 --> 01:39.115
and I kinda miss my husband.

01:39.242 --> 01:40.242
Yeah, me, too.

01:40.339 --> 01:41.349
He's a great guy.

01:41.469 --> 01:42.580
- That's funny.
- I'm sorry.

01:42.700 --> 01:43.906
Don't be sorry.
I know this is

01:44.000 --> 01:46.647
- a big opportunity for you...
- I am really sorry about-

01:46.820 --> 01:49.430
just for the money but to find out
what happened with your dad,

01:49.583 --> 01:51.780
you don't have to explain
I understand

01:51.900 --> 01:54.060
all the business you do
for the Darlings during the day

01:54.165 --> 01:56.204
and the noble work you do
with their money at night,

01:56.309 --> 01:58.380
I just feel like
there's no us anymore.

01:58.500 --> 01:59.792
It's all Darlings.

01:59.912 --> 02:02.541
Tell you what. We are gonna have
dinner tomorrow night.

02:02.664 --> 02:04.380
I'm not complaining. It's fine.

02:04.500 --> 02:06.305
- You're doing your job.
- Tomorrow night,

02:06.425 --> 02:08.114
just you and me, del posto.

02:08.234 --> 02:10.303
What do you say?
Kiki can stay with your mom.

02:13.000 --> 02:15.099
Say something.
Anything.

02:15.219 --> 02:17.280
You've just admitted to me

02:17.400 --> 02:20.085
that you've been an adulteress
for 40 years.

02:21.700 --> 02:24.080
Forgive me
if I'm short on words.

02:24.200 --> 02:25.871
- Where are you going?
- What?

02:26.000 --> 02:29.527
You haven't been in the same bed
with me for weeks.

02:29.668 --> 02:31.782
I've known that you've
suspected something,

02:31.902 --> 02:34.280
and I also knew
that you'd never say it.

02:34.400 --> 02:36.787
I mean, God forbid
that Tripp Darling

02:36.907 --> 02:39.046
should ever admit
to being...

02:40.600 --> 02:42.876
Affected by anything.

02:42.996 --> 02:44.603
Just tell me one thing.

02:45.500 --> 02:46.662
Our children,

02:47.626 --> 02:49.193
are they all mine?

02:49.592 --> 02:50.592
Yes.

02:51.600 --> 02:52.673
Absolutely.

02:54.300 --> 02:55.681
Oh, God.

02:55.801 --> 02:56.838
What?

02:57.200 --> 03:00.380
The thought that you can be
so sure...

03:00.500 --> 03:03.980
That such attention was paid
to such a prolonged,

03:04.121 --> 03:07.680
continuous insult
that you can say "absolutely,"

03:07.800 --> 03:10.614
as if it were a favor
you did me fondly.

03:13.402 --> 03:15.728
My God, Tish.
It's so sordid.

03:19.501 --> 03:21.665
- Wait, what's the place called?
- Bar known.

03:21.785 --> 03:24.080
Like the little dudes,
bar gnome?

03:24.200 --> 03:26.357
Not gnome, freak show.
Known.

03:26.487 --> 03:27.880
That's too bad.
I was psyched.

03:28.000 --> 03:30.215
I was gonna get, like,
a little red hat.

03:30.335 --> 03:32.110
Will you just come
with me anyway 'cause

03:32.251 --> 03:34.680
it's opening night,
and then there's this...

03:34.800 --> 03:36.902
What are you eating?

03:37.595 --> 03:38.638
Sausage.

03:39.225 --> 03:40.680
What?
What's the matter? Peta?

03:40.800 --> 03:42.580
No, I've just been
all queasy all morning

03:42.700 --> 03:44.271
and I'm, like,
a little bit spinny.

03:44.391 --> 03:45.856
Will you just tell me,
Jeremy,

03:45.976 --> 03:47.270
are you coming with me
or not?

03:47.390 --> 03:49.773
I gotta make sure Juliet's not
gonna be there. But as for me,

03:49.855 --> 03:52.613
tomorrow night?
Fo sho. I'm already there.

03:53.709 --> 03:55.680
I gotta go.
I'll see ya then, babe. Bye.

03:57.287 --> 03:58.327
What?

03:58.447 --> 04:00.579
- You were just talking to her.
- Who?

04:00.699 --> 04:03.280
- Your secret girlfriend.
- I have no girlfriend.

04:03.453 --> 04:06.880
Oh, yeah? Then who did you spend
600 grand on at bulgari,

04:07.005 --> 04:08.295
Justin Timberlake?

04:08.415 --> 04:10.134
All right, Jules,
I am telling the truth,

04:10.270 --> 04:12.800
I am... I'm pluto.

04:13.200 --> 04:16.180
I'm cold, distant
and alone.

04:16.300 --> 04:18.180
All right.
Well speaking of planets--

04:18.300 --> 04:20.077
pluto is not a planet
anymore.

04:20.208 --> 04:22.116
It will always be
a planet to me.

04:25.098 --> 04:26.280
What is this?

04:26.400 --> 04:28.359
An early birthday present.

04:32.648 --> 04:34.480
Hayden planetarium!

04:34.600 --> 04:36.780
- I got you the whole place.
- Get out.

04:36.900 --> 04:40.076
For rizzle. The entire cosmos
to yourself.

04:40.196 --> 04:42.448
Well, I don't have
a gift for you yet.

04:42.568 --> 04:44.164
It's kinda
three weeks early.

04:44.284 --> 04:45.480
Yes, you do.

04:45.600 --> 04:48.585
You see, there's this new club
opening tomorrow night.

04:48.705 --> 04:50.180
And they begged me,

04:50.300 --> 04:52.380
so I promised
to make an appearance,

04:52.500 --> 04:55.509
- and you can come with me.
- It's not bar known, is it?

04:55.629 --> 04:58.680
Oh, I know! It's like
the worst name ever, right?

04:58.800 --> 05:00.280
Yeah, it's
the absolute worst.

05:00.400 --> 05:01.640
You should just bail on it,

05:01.760 --> 05:03.243
you know?
Stay home, read a book.

05:04.613 --> 05:06.365
Are you on cold medicine?

05:06.639 --> 05:07.646
It's a new club.

05:07.766 --> 05:09.680
They asked me to be there.

05:09.800 --> 05:12.180
And for your information,
I read a book last night.

05:12.300 --> 05:13.967
Reading's a lifestyle, though.
It's an -

05:14.087 --> 05:16.780
Jeremy, I promised. I owe it
to them to be there.

05:16.900 --> 05:19.380
And now, thanks to me,
so do you.

05:19.500 --> 05:21.100
She is decided.

05:24.241 --> 05:26.394
I found something
very interesting, Tripp.

05:26.699 --> 05:28.980
Lookin' in
your dad's calendar?

05:29.100 --> 05:29.980
Yeah.

05:30.100 --> 05:33.180
In the wake of
the massive helpfulness

05:33.300 --> 05:34.423
from the police,

05:34.543 --> 05:36.633
I decided
to go over it again,

05:36.753 --> 05:38.680
check all the names,
all the dates,

05:38.800 --> 05:40.880
see if I could figure out,
you know, who gave dad

05:41.000 --> 05:43.480
all the information
on Simon elder and why.

05:43.600 --> 05:45.726
And my dad
had several meetings

05:45.846 --> 05:48.041
with someone he referred to
only by the letter "c."

05:48.448 --> 05:50.731
- "C"?
- I have no idea who it could be.

05:50.851 --> 05:52.780
Met him once a month,
sometimes twice.

05:52.900 --> 05:54.900
Hang on a second.

05:55.200 --> 05:57.080
There were a few times
I asked your dad

05:57.200 --> 05:59.757
to do some detective work
for me.

06:01.100 --> 06:03.380
Just after Kenneth
was assassinated

06:03.500 --> 06:05.300
was the first one.

06:05.700 --> 06:07.400
And there we others.

06:07.600 --> 06:09.380
When he wanted to...

06:09.500 --> 06:11.680
Maintain
a tasteful distance,

06:11.800 --> 06:15.100
he employed the services
of that man.

06:17.000 --> 06:18.280
"Harold Templeton"?

06:18.400 --> 06:20.234
Well, that's not
his real name.

06:20.380 --> 06:24.300
He was a spy in the 60s
for england...

06:24.500 --> 06:25.780
And China...

06:25.900 --> 06:27.080
And France.

06:27.200 --> 06:30.280
He even did some work
for Kennedy in Cuba.

06:30.400 --> 06:34.380
He managed to make himself
globally unpopular.

06:34.500 --> 06:36.772
You can't mention this
to anyone, not even Lisa.

06:39.100 --> 06:40.680
How do I find him?

06:40.800 --> 06:43.200
Well, there's
a little vineyard in--

06:43.400 --> 06:44.880
just outside of Milan.

06:45.000 --> 06:46.980
It's near our summer place in Italy

06:47.100 --> 06:48.375
where you
and your dad used to

06:48.495 --> 06:50.600
spend some time with us.

06:51.000 --> 06:52.980
They make
a great little wine.

06:53.100 --> 06:54.612
Chiavennasca.

06:55.700 --> 06:58.580
Anyway,
if I remember correctly,

07:00.000 --> 07:01.724
you go to that vineyard...

07:03.200 --> 07:04.988
You ask for that wine...

07:06.127 --> 07:07.766
- Slightly chilled.
- Wait a second.

07:07.886 --> 07:10.514
Are you asking me to go
to Italy to find this guy?

07:10.634 --> 07:11.480
Yeah.

07:11.600 --> 07:13.980
No, I mean, that's where
Dutch always started out

07:14.100 --> 07:15.980
when he was trying
to track him down.

07:16.100 --> 07:17.780
He keeps a very low profile.

07:17.900 --> 07:20.980
Anyway, you ask for the wine,
then see what happens.

07:21.100 --> 07:23.980
If you manage to locate
Mr. Templeton,

07:24.100 --> 07:26.480
he might be able
to explain to you

07:26.600 --> 07:28.328
the origins of the...

07:28.900 --> 07:30.335
Elder dossier.

07:30.455 --> 07:31.456
Who knows?

07:31.576 --> 07:33.997
He may even be able
to tell you who "c" is.

07:34.900 --> 07:35.970
Okay.

07:36.900 --> 07:38.208
I'll go to Italy.

07:39.184 --> 07:40.011
Nick.

07:40.136 --> 07:41.008
Yeah.

07:41.128 --> 07:43.513
Snag a bottle fome,
will you?

07:43.649 --> 07:44.658
Will do.

07:44.760 --> 07:46.180
Chiavennasca.

07:46.300 --> 07:48.765
Chiavennasca. Got it.

08:01.741 --> 08:02.946
Aren't those to die for?

08:03.066 --> 08:05.780
It's like they're made
out of George Clooney.

08:05.900 --> 08:07.784
- How much?
- $1,200.

08:07.904 --> 08:10.780
12...
$1,200?

08:10.900 --> 08:12.580
Do they come
with a kidney?

08:12.700 --> 08:14.504
No, they come
with each other.

08:16.100 --> 08:18.846
What kind of person
spends $1,200 on shoes?

08:19.700 --> 08:20.586
Lisa.

08:25.600 --> 08:26.925
What are you doing here?

08:27.045 --> 08:29.356
Picked up a suit for Nick.
We're going out tomorrow night,

08:29.476 --> 08:32.280
- so I just kinda thought-
- then you have to buy those shoes.

08:32.400 --> 08:35.395
- No, actually--
- oh, yes, actually.

08:35.515 --> 08:37.179
And do get them in raspberry.
I have them.

08:37.299 --> 08:39.179
- I wear them all the time.
- I can't buy shoes

08:39.299 --> 08:41.080
that cost as much
as car insurance.

08:41.200 --> 08:44.528
Lisa, honey, don't be
so financially resistant, okay?

08:45.400 --> 08:47.000
It's just money.

08:53.000 --> 08:54.780
You did a little
shopping today, huh?

08:54.900 --> 08:56.380
No, I did
a little browsing.

08:56.500 --> 08:58.580
Karen Darling
did the shopping.

08:58.700 --> 09:00.880
Right after I told you
our whole world was Darlings,

09:01.000 --> 09:02.480
- Darlings everywhere...
- Yeah.

09:02.600 --> 09:04.480
I ran into her.
We chatted.

09:04.600 --> 09:07.280
- 3 hours later, those shoes showed up.
- Well, that was thoughtful.

09:07.400 --> 09:09.764
Yeah, I'm sure a lot of thought
went into that purchase.

09:09.884 --> 09:11.456
What's the problem?
She sent you a gift.

09:11.545 --> 09:12.565
She does stuff like that.

09:12.685 --> 09:14.280
Why would Karen Darling
send me a gift?

09:14.400 --> 09:17.020
Hey, Lise, you're starting
to sound a little paranoid.

09:17.140 --> 09:19.480
Ok? Sometimes a shoe
is just a shoe.

09:20.068 --> 09:21.402
And sometimes
it's a bomb.

09:22.400 --> 09:24.180
So much for
our night out, huh?

09:24.300 --> 09:26.780
Instead of a great meal
at del posto

09:26.900 --> 09:28.380
and a night of wild sex...

09:28.500 --> 09:32.080
Which I was really
looking forward to...

09:32.200 --> 09:36.680
I get leftovers and a DVD
and you get a, what,

09:36.800 --> 09:38.980
a whirlwind trip
to some villa in Italy

09:39.100 --> 09:40.669
to pick up one bottle
of chiave--

09:40.828 --> 09:41.920
chiavennasca.

09:45.007 --> 09:46.285
Why don't you
come with me?

09:46.407 --> 09:47.852
- I can't. It's work.
- Why not?

09:47.986 --> 09:50.180
- This is work.
- So what if it's work? Come on.

09:50.300 --> 09:51.755
It's a private jet.
There's room.

09:52.074 --> 09:54.848
You know, your mom can watch
Kiki over the weekend.

09:54.970 --> 09:56.680
- Let's go to Italy.
- Yeah?

09:57.514 --> 10:01.285
Look, it's totally free,
and for two days, no Darlings.

10:02.900 --> 10:04.818
No Darlings.

10:23.127 --> 10:25.426
See? Reading. Happy now?

10:25.546 --> 10:26.623
Very nice.

10:31.760 --> 10:33.350
"Babes in toyland"?

10:33.470 --> 10:35.135
I felt bad I didn't have
a gift for you,

10:35.257 --> 10:37.266
- so I rented out the whole angelika.
- For tonight?

10:37.409 --> 10:39.940
- Yeah.
- Well, that is so sweet of you.

10:40.227 --> 10:42.080
- Oh, I know.
- But I can't go.

10:42.200 --> 10:43.680
You have to.
The thing is set.

10:43.800 --> 10:45.980
Well, we have to go
to the club tonight.

10:46.100 --> 10:48.574
I gave my word.
My word is my bond.

10:48.694 --> 10:51.380
Anyways, when I decided
I wanted to read for the remake,

10:51.500 --> 10:54.180
I decided that
I couldn't watch the original

10:54.300 --> 10:57.380
because Annette funicello
is so iconic.

10:57.500 --> 10:58.880
I didn't want to copy.

10:59.000 --> 11:01.980
But it was a really
picturesque thought.

11:02.244 --> 11:03.447
Thanks.

11:08.237 --> 11:10.180
Why aren't you dressed
for school today, Gustav?

11:10.300 --> 11:11.313
I don't want to go.

11:11.433 --> 11:12.980
Is that how they do things
in Sweden?

11:13.100 --> 11:15.780
School's like a tea party,
you go if you want?

11:15.900 --> 11:17.900
What happened to your face?

11:19.516 --> 11:21.180
- Bully hit me.
- Did you hit back?

11:21.300 --> 11:23.480
- Jesus says don't hit back.
- Says who?

11:23.600 --> 11:25.100
My mommy.

11:27.847 --> 11:28.889
Your mommy?

11:29.717 --> 11:31.721
You mean your mommy
who's dead?

11:35.600 --> 11:36.449
Yeah.

11:37.400 --> 11:38.459
Poor kid.

11:38.800 --> 11:40.524
She's in a better place now.

11:41.700 --> 11:43.980
Bully or no bully,
still has to go to school.

11:44.100 --> 11:46.580
Okay, but I'm gonna
get terrorized.

11:46.700 --> 11:49.480
Gustav, the world
is full of bullies

11:49.600 --> 11:50.980
and always will be.

11:51.100 --> 11:54.080
- You can't live in fear.
- What am I supposed to do?

11:54.200 --> 11:56.433
What do you think?
Fight back.

11:56.553 --> 11:58.466
Like David and goliath.
You find a weakness

11:58.588 --> 12:01.500
and you take advantage.
There's your Bible truth for today.

12:17.300 --> 12:21.080
Because I share your passion
for the truth, that's why.

12:21.200 --> 12:23.528
Well, what makes you so sure
the painting's a forgery?

12:23.648 --> 12:25.280
Peter, I don't want
to do this to you.

12:25.400 --> 12:26.980
You've been our doctor
for years.

12:27.100 --> 12:29.380
But Tish and I were passing
through David Frank's gallery

12:29.500 --> 12:32.380
on our way to meet Karen
about a week ago...

12:32.500 --> 12:34.719
I don't know,
maybe it was the light.

12:35.400 --> 12:37.980
And I saw a speck
of prussian blue

12:38.100 --> 12:39.180
in "das kind"--

12:39.300 --> 12:40.574
your painting.

12:41.158 --> 12:42.263
Prussian blue? I...

12:42.389 --> 12:43.780
Yeah, the pigment.

12:43.900 --> 12:47.467
It had not yet been invented
in engel's lifetime.

12:48.600 --> 12:50.756
So I became suspicious.

12:52.100 --> 12:53.880
There's a forger in Belgium

12:54.000 --> 12:56.680
who's becoming quietly famous
in some circles

12:56.800 --> 12:58.408
for this sort of thing.

12:59.800 --> 13:00.833
I'm sorry...

13:02.300 --> 13:04.380
But your painting is a fake.

13:04.500 --> 13:06.620
Stretfield's guaranteed
$6 million.

13:07.700 --> 13:10.341
That painting's our exit strategy.

13:13.900 --> 13:17.952
You've been Tish's o. B.-G. Y. N.
For over three decades.

13:20.300 --> 13:22.552
And this is a little secret.

13:24.600 --> 13:25.605
Trust me.

13:27.096 --> 13:29.604
This is going to go
with me to my grave.

13:31.000 --> 13:32.264
I am curious...

13:32.778 --> 13:33.780
About what?

13:33.900 --> 13:37.138
In all the years that you've
been delivering our children...

13:39.500 --> 13:40.880
Have you ever been aware

13:41.000 --> 13:43.468
that any of them
might not have been mine?

13:44.912 --> 13:46.877
You might look into that for me.

13:46.997 --> 13:48.571
Yeah, sure. I could...

13:49.264 --> 13:50.835
Get you an answer on that,

13:50.968 --> 13:54.042
- sometime next week if you like.
- Tomorrow would be best.

14:10.453 --> 14:12.380
If Natalie Kimpton's
gonna be here all night

14:12.500 --> 14:13.680
with Ryan casdale,

14:13.800 --> 14:17.080
this place is over
before it even began.

14:17.200 --> 14:18.380
What is that?

14:18.500 --> 14:22.162
The old vodka
in the water bottle routine?

14:22.282 --> 14:24.289
That is so 2004.

14:25.900 --> 14:27.960
Does she think
she's fooling anyone?

