30:14.300 --> 30:15.677
and it's never
going to come true.

30:15.821 --> 30:17.931
So stay away from my husband
and...

30:18.053 --> 30:19.584
Stay out of my way.

30:27.689 --> 30:29.509
- Who was that, baby?
- Nobody.

30:30.735 --> 30:32.662
Make me a drink,
would you?

30:53.200 --> 30:54.600
Go away.

30:55.899 --> 30:57.079
We need to talk.

30:57.293 --> 30:59.052
I'm not speaking to you,
traitor.

31:04.700 --> 31:06.624
Juliet... I love her.

31:06.949 --> 31:07.972
Love?

31:11.400 --> 31:13.366
Okay, I really like her.

31:13.486 --> 31:14.562
Like?

31:16.000 --> 31:17.556
I'm moderately interest--

31:17.686 --> 31:19.205
why can't you be cool
about this?

31:19.325 --> 31:20.980
Because she doesn't care
about you.

31:21.100 --> 31:22.911
She's only using you to get at me.

31:23.444 --> 31:25.680
Now I get it. Yeah.
It's about you. Right?

31:25.800 --> 31:28.756
- Everything is just all about you.
- I'm just trying to protect you.

31:28.876 --> 31:30.824
You don't have to!
You're the one running around

31:30.920 --> 31:32.680
telling everyone
you want to be independent.

31:32.800 --> 31:34.342
You want your own career,
to move out.

31:34.462 --> 31:36.380
You can't even let
your twin brother date someone

31:36.500 --> 31:38.558
you had a stupid fight with
over bangs? Why?

31:38.678 --> 31:42.437
Because it makes you feel so lonely
and freaked out and threatened.

31:43.028 --> 31:44.182
I mean, bangs?

31:50.953 --> 31:52.934
I feel
so far from home.

31:53.711 --> 31:55.950
Yeah,
I know what you mean.

31:56.070 --> 31:59.704
I hate that we can't just get on
a plane right now and go.

32:01.458 --> 32:02.580
Well, we could,

32:02.700 --> 32:05.080
but we'd have to fly
with Karen and Freddy.

32:05.200 --> 32:07.500
Well, they have
their private jet.

32:08.000 --> 32:10.480
We are flying back like--
like normal people

32:10.600 --> 32:13.080
with... lines and security

32:13.200 --> 32:15.136
and peanuts and back pain

32:15.256 --> 32:17.617
and... life.

32:22.600 --> 32:24.000
God...

32:24.200 --> 32:27.500
It's...
Weird being married.

32:28.800 --> 32:30.568
It's so weird.

32:31.800 --> 32:33.500
Yeah...

32:34.700 --> 32:36.200
It is.

32:37.600 --> 32:39.080
Promise me something.

32:39.200 --> 32:40.200
What?

32:41.550 --> 32:43.870
Promise me that we are never
going to have to come

32:44.011 --> 32:47.200
all the way to Italy for a stupid
bottle of wine again, please.

33:00.829 --> 33:02.068
Lisa...

33:03.500 --> 33:05.798
We didn't come here
for a bottle of wine.

33:07.600 --> 33:10.380
I needed to meet with a guy
who did some work for my dad.

33:10.500 --> 33:11.780
When did you do that?

33:11.900 --> 33:14.200
When I went down
to the wine cellar.

33:15.200 --> 33:17.000
He's a spy.

33:17.601 --> 33:18.880
It's a long story.

33:19.000 --> 33:22.475
I look forward to hearing
about it halfway over the Atlantic.

33:26.394 --> 33:28.480
You know, I count on you
for so much, Lise.

33:28.600 --> 33:29.900
You know that?

33:31.331 --> 33:33.464
- A little.
- When I look at you,

33:33.584 --> 33:36.634
here's this perfect line
from me through you

33:36.754 --> 33:38.505
to the center of the earth.

33:39.300 --> 33:41.500
You keep me connected
to everything.

33:42.900 --> 33:44.392
You do the same for me.

33:45.484 --> 33:47.080
And Kiki does it
for both of us.

33:47.200 --> 33:50.083
It's a...
It's a beautiful thing.

33:50.224 --> 33:52.646
You know, I don't think my dad
felt that way about anyone.

33:52.780 --> 33:54.780
You don't think he felt
that way about you?

33:54.900 --> 33:56.297
I don't know.

33:58.400 --> 33:59.866
I really don't.

34:04.200 --> 34:06.377
Lei vuole fare l'amore?

34:08.000 --> 34:09.980
You picked up
a little Italian?

34:10.100 --> 34:11.380
Enough to get by.

34:11.500 --> 34:12.500
Yeah?

34:30.002 --> 34:31.878
Victoria,
would you excuse us?

34:31.998 --> 34:32.998
Yes, sir.

34:33.097 --> 34:35.985
Thank you so much...

34:36.914 --> 34:38.199
For all you do.

34:45.687 --> 34:47.900
Silver up to snuff?

34:52.800 --> 34:54.600
It's getting there.

35:02.500 --> 35:03.760
We need to talk.

35:04.608 --> 35:05.768
What's that?

35:08.390 --> 35:10.186
D. N. A. Results.

35:11.793 --> 35:12.897
You lied to me.

35:13.017 --> 35:14.857
What the hell
have you done?

35:16.400 --> 35:19.080
I found out
what I needed to now.

35:19.200 --> 35:21.480
I found out
the only way that I could

35:21.600 --> 35:24.659
give the fact that my wife
doesn't tell me the truth.

35:25.700 --> 35:26.801
So...

35:27.500 --> 35:28.537
So you know?

35:29.500 --> 35:31.318
I haven't read
the results.

35:32.200 --> 35:33.246
I won't.

35:34.800 --> 35:36.671
I want to hear it
from you.

35:39.300 --> 35:40.845
Which of our children

35:41.904 --> 35:43.132
isn't mine?

35:44.401 --> 35:47.139
Which one is Dutch's?

35:55.380 --> 35:56.536
I'll tell you.

35:58.700 --> 36:01.487
But you've got to promise me
nothing will change...

36:01.900 --> 36:03.572
As far as the children
are concerned.

36:03.692 --> 36:06.246
I don't have to
promise you anything.

36:07.113 --> 36:08.494
You took my life--

36:09.700 --> 36:12.580
you took my life
that I placed in your hands

36:12.700 --> 36:15.680
to help me carry it
safely to the grave,

36:15.833 --> 36:19.103
and you laid it on every bedside
table you could find

36:19.223 --> 36:20.880
while you pursued
whatever it was

36:21.000 --> 36:23.380
you were pursuing
all those years.

36:23.500 --> 36:25.980
I hope it was
the obliteration of yourself,

36:26.100 --> 36:28.617
because, my God,
that's what you've achieved.

36:29.200 --> 36:31.500
Just tell me the truth...

36:31.700 --> 36:33.583
Or leave right now.

36:33.783 --> 36:35.000
I mean it.

36:37.200 --> 36:39.942
You're the only woman
in the world for me, Tish.

36:41.800 --> 36:43.180
But can't live every day

36:43.300 --> 36:45.946
with my face being pushed
into this filth.

36:47.945 --> 36:50.600
If you want me
in that bed tonight...

36:53.800 --> 36:55.200
Tell me.

37:01.700 --> 37:03.215
All right.

37:04.800 --> 37:06.218
All right.

37:11.300 --> 37:13.142
I'll tell you.

37:24.600 --> 37:28.000
No, chora!
You're hurting me!

37:28.852 --> 37:29.855
What's the matter?

37:29.975 --> 37:31.362
You gotta be nicer to me,
or else

37:31.467 --> 37:34.880
- I'll tell Mei ling hwa the truth.
- What is this, blackmail?

37:35.000 --> 37:37.180
You told me to find
a weakness.

37:37.300 --> 37:39.292
You cunning little turd.

37:43.200 --> 37:44.217
What do you want?

37:47.800 --> 37:49.296
Get off of me!

37:50.511 --> 37:52.518
Help me. Please.

37:57.700 --> 37:58.736
Hi, chora.

38:00.286 --> 38:02.612
Those are nice hair clips.
What are those, bumblebees?

38:02.732 --> 38:03.753
Hornets.

38:04.200 --> 38:06.824
You know God, chora?
Well, he's sorta my boss.

38:07.200 --> 38:08.910
And you see that boy
over there?

38:10.600 --> 38:11.702
God told me

38:12.369 --> 38:14.456
you're not being
very nice to him.

38:15.100 --> 38:16.677
And God is so disappointed.

38:17.200 --> 38:19.795
So from now on, he wants
you two to be friends.

38:19.915 --> 38:23.480
Otherwise you're gonna burn
in hell for eternity,

38:23.600 --> 38:25.919
and eternity's
a very long time.

38:29.891 --> 38:30.934
Are we clear?

38:32.303 --> 38:33.414
Good girl.

38:42.800 --> 38:46.080
So I'm assuming you met
our friend--Mr. Templeton?

38:46.200 --> 38:47.680
Yes, I did.

38:47.800 --> 38:49.480
And what did he have
to say?

38:49.600 --> 38:51.280
Well, you were right.

38:51.400 --> 38:53.488
He put the elder file
together for dad.

38:54.000 --> 38:55.700
Yeah, I figured.

38:59.400 --> 39:00.847
To your good health.

39:01.600 --> 39:02.700
Cheers.

39:10.400 --> 39:12.180
So what do you think?

39:12.300 --> 39:13.390
Be honest.

39:14.900 --> 39:16.922
My father was working
for someone else.

39:25.300 --> 39:27.905
Could it be that "c"
that was in his calendar?

39:28.025 --> 39:29.553
I don't know. Maybe.

39:30.700 --> 39:33.534
But he was gathering
that information for someone.

39:33.663 --> 39:35.997
And Templeton stopped helping
when he found out about it.

39:36.117 --> 39:37.180
So that dossier,

39:37.300 --> 39:39.490
all that information
on Simon elder,

39:40.400 --> 39:44.171
that wasn't just Dutch
doing... diligent work

39:44.291 --> 39:45.323
on my behalf?

39:46.000 --> 39:47.700
No, it doesn't look like it.

39:52.400 --> 39:54.880
He was gathering information
about you as well.

39:55.000 --> 39:56.323
- About me?
- Yeah.

40:02.600 --> 40:04.580
- I'm sorry.
- Why? You didn't do it.

40:04.700 --> 40:07.400
- I know, but he--
- no, you're you.

40:07.648 --> 40:10.740
And you're good.
That's true.

40:13.700 --> 40:14.754
Well...

40:16.591 --> 40:18.276
Anything happen
while I was gone?

40:20.300 --> 40:21.816
Nothing unexpected.

40:23.300 --> 40:26.246
Things continue
to reveal themselves.

40:28.800 --> 40:30.050
Reality.

40:42.000 --> 40:44.127
I like looking
at the stars because...

40:46.200 --> 40:47.754
You know, they're so...

40:48.300 --> 40:50.529
Hot and fiery
and explosive,

40:51.100 --> 40:53.380
but it feels totally safe
and totally exciting

40:53.500 --> 40:55.080
all at the same time,
you know?

40:55.200 --> 40:58.200
I never thought a girl
could make me feel that way.

41:02.144 --> 41:03.251
But you do.

41:06.600 --> 41:09.300
Looking at you is like
looking at the stars.

41:12.481 --> 41:14.880
You make me feel like I'm--
I'm a part of everything,

41:15.000 --> 41:16.500
like I have a place.

41:18.845 --> 41:20.601
Are you being for real?

41:23.819 --> 41:25.357
Natalie, I'm "for realer"
with you

41:25.531 --> 41:27.274
than I've ever been
with anybody.

41:29.300 --> 41:30.444
Me, too.

41:33.500 --> 41:34.824
Maybe we're in love.

41:38.800 --> 41:40.121
I think we are.

41:50.500 --> 41:51.580
Jeremy.

41:51.700 --> 41:52.700
Yeah.

41:55.700 --> 41:56.982
I'm pregnant.

42:09.600 --> 42:11.000
That's wet.

42:20.778 --> 42:21.966
Nicholas George?

42:23.000 --> 42:24.000
Yeah.

42:25.900 --> 42:27.400
Simon elder.

42:28.000 --> 42:29.600
Want to go for a ride?

42:30.547 --> 42:31.379
Sure.
